extends ../_template.pug

block title
  | Alpakka components

block page
  include _title.pug

  div.boxes.grid
    div.box
      h2 Firmware
      p The open source firmware for the controller, for the Raspberry Pi Pico.
      p Compiled builds with the latest version are also available.
      table.data
        tr
          td Alpakka firmware source code
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_firmware') Repository
        tr
          td Alpakka firmware latest build
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_firmware/releases/latest') Repository

    div.box
      h2 Printed Circuit Board
      p The main board where all the buttons, gyro, thumbstick, LEDs and most other electronics are.
      p Read the documentation about making an order to PCB manufacturer companies.
      table.data
        tr
          td Alpakka PCB KiCad schematics
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_pcb') Repository
        tr
          td Alpakka PCB ready-to-order files
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_pcb/releases/latest') Repository

    div.box
      h2 Microcontroller
      p This small device contains the processor, memory, and other important components for the Alpakka controller to work. It is attached to the main PCB.
      div
        table.data
          tr
            td Raspberry Pi Pico
            td: +ax('https://www.raspberrypi.com/products/raspberry-pi-pico/') Visit website

    div.box
      h2 Case and buttons
      p The front and back part of the case, and all its buttons and triggers. The base models are made in Blender, but is also possible to use the .stl or .m3f files to 3D print it directly.
      table.data
        tr
          td Blender project with source 3D models
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_case') Repository
        tr
          td STL and M3F files ready for 3D printing
          td: +ax('https://github.com/inputlabs/alpakka_case/releases/latest') Repository

    div.box
      h2 3D printer filament
      p Selected premium filaments from different manufacturers, that we tried and recommend.
      p Polylactic acid (PLA) is a biodegradable material usually made from corn waste, popular for 3D printing due to its low melting temperature and strength.
      table.data
        tr
          td Prusament PLA (in many colors)
          td: +ax('https://www.prusa3d.com/category/prusament-pla') Visit website
        tr
          td Protopasta PLA Conductive
          td: +ax('https://www.proto-pasta.com/collections/conductive/products/conductive-pla') Visit website

    div.box
      h2 Electronics
      p Thru-hole components that are not usually soldered by the PCB manufacturer, so you may want to solder them yourself. Also to replace aged components. See #[+a('manual/specs') Specs].
      table.data
        tr
          td Thumbstick (1x)
          td: +ax('https://tech.alpsalpine.com/e/products/detail/RKJXV122400R/') Visit website
        tr
          td Directional hat (1x)
          td: +ax('https://tech.alpsalpine.com/e/products/detail/RKJXM1015004/') Visit website
        tr
          td Rotary encoder (1x)
          td: +ax('https://tech.alpsalpine.com/e/products/detail/EC10E1220503/') Visit website
        tr
          td Forward buttons / shoulders (2x)
          td: +ax('https://tech.alpsalpine.com/e/products/detail/SKHHLNA010/') Visit website
        tr
          td Back buttons / triggers (4x)
          td: +ax('https://tech.alpsalpine.com/e/products/detail/SKQGAFE010/') Visit website

    div.box
      h2 Bolts and nuts
      p M2.5 bolts and nuts to hold the case together, and as pivot point for the triggers.
      p: i Links for reference, components with the same specs from other shops will also work.
      table.data
        tr
          td M2.5 DIN-912 Hex-socket 12 mm (2x)
          td: +ax('https://www.mcmaster.com/92290A062/') Visit website
        tr
          td M2.5 DIN-912 Hex-socket 25 mm (6x)
          td: +ax('https://www.mcmaster.com/92290A753/') Visit website
        tr
          td M2.5 DIN-934 Hex nut (8x)
          td: +ax('https://www.mcmaster.com/91828A113/') Visit website

    div.box
      h2 Developer kit
      p Basic tools required for hacking the Alpakka. For more details check Alpakka's #[+a('manual/dev') Developer] manual.
      p: i Links for reference, components with the same specs from other shops will also work.
      table.data
        tr
          td USB to TTL serial cable
          td: +ax('https://www.adafruit.com/product/954') Visit website
        tr
          td JST PH 4-pin cable
          td: +ax('https://www.adafruit.com/product/3955') Visit website


